## YouTube-Video-Info-For-Splunk ##

       Original Author: Mark Hill - Intalock
       Current maintainers: Mark Hill - Intalock
       Version/Date: 1.0.2 / Jun 25, 2018
       Has index-time ops: false

## Update History ##
----------------------------
       1.0.2 Jun 28, 2018
       --------
       First release.

A custom command that adds metadata from google based on a youtube video_id

How it works:
This Splunk App provides a custom command that takes the video_id from a youtube URL and uses the youtube API to get information about the video such as title, category and view count.

Before first use, configure the google API key using the app's setup page.

Simply define which splunk field is your 'video_id' from the extracted data, and call it 'video_id' and then pass that to the ytinfo command

| eval video_id=v | ytinfo

Example 1:

| makeresults | eval video_id="dQw4w9WgXcQ" | ytinfo | lookup youtube_categories.csv video_category

Note that the result above has been enriched with a lookup, translating category ID into a friendly category name.

Example 2:

index=proxy_logs request=*www.youtube.com/watch?v* | eval video_id=v | ytinfo

Where is the video_id in the YouTube URL?
The video is in the url it typically - "http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TheVideoID", "http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oHg5SJYRHA0"

Splunk might already be extracting the "v" since it does so automatically with key=value pairs in URLs, so simply check the extracted fields for "v"

What fields are available for me after the lookup?
video_title -- The title of the video
video_category -- The category of the video on youtube
view_count -- How many times the video has been viewed on youtube


